This paper deals with wireless communication and signal processing, which are core topics in the field of Information Theory (cs.IT). The use of multiple antennas and precoding techniques also suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The study of the MIMO switch and its optimization for signal-to-noise ratios involves system-level analysis and control, which could fall under the sub-category of Systems and Control (cs.SY). The use of matrices and algorithms for precoder design suggests that the paper could also belong to the sub-category of Multimedia (cs.MM) or Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE).
